        <div class="privacy-text">
            <h2>Book Inclusion Process</h2>

            <p>
                Axiom has a set of processes or criteria for including books to it database, and for the book to be accepted, the book must pass all criteria if not will be rejected for coverage. The process typically follows these key steps:
            </p> 
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <h3>Submission and Application: </h3>Authors, publishers, or representatives submit applications for book inclusion in the index, providing comprehensive details about the book, including its title, author(s), publication information, synopsis, table of contents, and relevance to the academic field.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h3>Initial Screening: </h3>The submitted applications undergo an initial review by the editorial team to assess their alignment with the inclusion criteria. This stage ensures that the books meet the basic prerequisites for further evaluation.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h3>Content Evaluation: </h3>Books passing the initial screening undergo a thorough content evaluation by subject matter experts or reviewers. This evaluation assesses the academic rigor, originality, contribution to the field, clarity of content, and relevance to scholarly research.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h3>Quality Assessment:</h3>The editorial team conducts a quality assessment, considering factors such as the credibility of the author(s), the publisher's reputation, adherence to ethical standards, and the book's potential impact on academic discourse.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h3>Editorial Decision-making: </h3>Based on the evaluations and assessments, the editorial board or review committee deliberates on the inclusion or exclusion of the book from the index. This decision-making process is guided by the established inclusion criteria, ensuring consistency and maintaining the index's credibility.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h3>Notification and Feedback: </h3> Authors or representatives of the submitted books receive notification of the decision along with feedback or recommendations if applicable. Transparent communication fosters understanding and encourages improvements if necessary.

                </li>
                <li>
                    <h3>Regular Updates and Reviews: </h3> Included books are periodically reviewed to ensure they continue to meet the index's standards. This ongoing review process allows for the maintenance of a curated collection of high-quality academic books.

                </li>

            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<!-- Privacy Section End -->
